Sharon Edwards was last seen between 10pm and 11pm on March 14 in Grafton . 
  She was a teacher at a local school but did not turn up to work on March 16 . 
  Her car was left in her driveway and her clothes were thrown in the washing . 
  There was no sign of forced entry at her home and police are treating her disappearance as a homicide . 
  The 55-year-old has no history of mental illness . 
  Her son said his family is struggling to cope with her disappearance . 
  Ms Edwards was missing for almost a month before her body was found . 
  She has not accessed her bank or social media accounts . 
  The teacher was missing from her home on the NSW north coast . 
 